posts.name: Martin Pirringer
posts.cooked:
We are getting ready for a competition this weekend and we are a new team - I have some experience and am stumped We got a roborio 1 donated and formated it successfully to team 9999 (waiting for some $$$ to get - hopefully - our real number) that worked great, Configured the radio and installed WPILIB and the game tools. The driver station sees the robot. We first tried some code that should work - Arcaded drive - and when that did not show just tried to deploy a sample code that comes with WPILIB

So 1,) Create new project, select sample code and the xbox controller 2.) Build project no error 3.) Deploy it 20231109_1509301 1920×1081 213 KB So according to VSCode it deploys fine 20231109_1510061 1920×1081 158 KB And the driver station shows communication green, Joystick green and No robot code. And nothing in the log Last time I did set up a rio a zillion years ago I had to terminal in and deploy the JRE to the roborio. I cant find any info as to having to do that and if I missed it it would be great if someone could point me to it.

20231109_1509301 1920×1081 213 KB

20231109_1509301 1920×1081 213 KB

20231109_1510061 1920×1081 158 KB

20231109_1510061 1920×1081 158 KB

I can’t find any error messages and tried to deploy

1.) With USB connection 2.) With ethernet connected to the router/radio

WIFI is turned off when deploying through USB I not only turned wifi off but also the ethernet port and disconnected it (its a usb to ethernet dongle as the laptop does not have a ethernet port laptop has win11 on it

Also tried a different laptop with win10 on it.

Reformatted the roborio a couple of times with no error.

Any help would be appreciated.

posts.name: Gerardo Inzunza
posts.cooked: Did you run it as start up after you built it and deployed it

posts.name: Thad House
posts.cooked: The name of the folder is what is used for the output Jar. It’s very possible the startup code doesn’t like the apostrophe in the folder name. It also sometimes has issue with spaces. Try moving the folder to a project with just normal characters and try deploying again. Delete the build folder when you rename the folder.

posts.name: Martin Pirringer
posts.cooked: created a new project with a simple 8 char folder and same thing

posts.name: Peter Johnson
posts.cooked:
The “run as start up” thing is for LabVIEW, not text-based languages.

The JRE is also auto-deployed the first time you deploy a Java program to the robot.

One thing to check would be the “No App” setting, it shouldn’t be set because you just imaged the Rio, but it’s something to check–you can see it by opening a web browser to roborio-9999-frc.local and looking for a checkbox labeled “No App” or similar and making sure it’s unchecked.
